{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"If you want to bring your creativity, passion, and technical expertise to the iBookstore, it may seem like there’s a vast array of web technologies to master. Gain a solid understanding of the HTML, CSS, and DOM technologies that are most relevant to book development, whether you’re creating a book with EPUB or building a custom widget for iBooks Author. See how to create beautiful text that is always laid out perfectly, gain a deep understanding of CSS positioning to create exceptional fixed-layout books, find out how to enrich your content with CSS animations, and learn which DOM operations are critical to adding enhancements with ease."}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2012\/515\/","overridingTitle":"Read Transcript"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC12"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC12-515-HTML-CSS-and-DOM-for-Book-Authors","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc12-515-html-css-and-dom-for-book-authors"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by reading the transcript and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"article","sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"role":"sampleCode","title":"HTML, CSS, and DOM for Book Authors","roleHeading":"WWDC12","modules":[{"name